                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GEORGE FRY</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-2448-18430821" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-2448-18430821" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2448-18430821" type="age" value="38"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2448-18430821" type="surname" value="LANGLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2448-18430821" type="given" value="MARIA"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">MARIA LANGLEY</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18430821-2448-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2448-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2448-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> steal<lb></lb>ing, on the <rs id="t18430821-cd-200" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2448-offence-1 t18430821-cd-200"></join>15th of February</rs>, 1 table cloth, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 1 flannel shirt, 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 candlestick, 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 1 flat iron, 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and 1 blanket, 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18430821-name-1208" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1208" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1208" type="surname" value="LYONS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1208" type="given" value="JEREMIAH"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2448-offence-1 t18430821-name-1208"></join>Jeremiah Lyons</persName>: and that Langley had been before convicted.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1209" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1209" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1209" type="surname" value="LYONS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1209" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY LYONS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Jeremiah Lyons, and live in Long-lane, Ratcliffe. The prisoners both lodged at my house—when they went away I missed a blanket, a table-cloth, a flannel shirt, and a flat-iron—these are them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Fry.</hi> I have a pension from the East India Company—it was due on the 22nd of August—there was 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. due to me. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> He owes me 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—the key was sent home by another lodger, and I found all the things gone—there were not any things borrowed of me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Langley.</hi> Every article here has been lent to us. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, they have not—I lent her the flat-iron to iron with, not to get a quartern of rum on—the flannel shirt was not lent to you to pledge with a piece of diaper.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1210" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1210" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1210" type="surname" value="MURRAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1210" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE MURRAY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable 68 K.</hi>) I took the prisoners. The duplicate of the flat-iron was given me by Langley, and two duplicates of a table cloth and a flannel shirt were given me by Mrs. Lyons—Langley said what she had done was under the direction of Fry that Mrs. Lyons had given her permission to pledge these articles.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1211" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1211" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1211" type="surname" value="ALLEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1211" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS ALLEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker. I produce a table cloth and a flannel shirt, which were pledged by Langley in the name of "Fry, 7, High-street"—they correspond with the duplicate I have.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Langley. Q.</hi> Do you remember my separating the shirt from the diaper? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—but I recollect Mrs. Lyons saying, when she came to make inquiries, that there was a flat-iron, a shirt, and some other articles, but the table cloth she had lent to Langley—I did not tell the magistrate that the prosecutrix said that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1212" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1212" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1212" type="surname" value="LYONS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1212" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY LYONS</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I did not tell Allen that I had lent the cloth to Langley—the policeman was with me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1213" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1213" type="surname" value="MURRAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1213" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE MURRAY</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I went with Mrs. Lyons—I did not hear her tell Allen so.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Langley's Defence.</hi> The whole of the articles were lent to us some months ago when my husband was out of employ—the flannel shirt was first pawned with a piece of diaper, which I redeemed—she allowed me to pledge the bed</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210175"></xptr>
               <p>clothes from December till the week we were taken—the used to lend her lodgers articles to pledge, and then give them into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1214" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1214" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1214" type="surname" value="PALMER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1214" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES PALMER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-inspector.</hi>) I produce a certificate of Langley's former conviction, which I got from Mr. Clark's office—the prisoner is the person.</p>
